  "text": "A dominating set of a graph is a set of vertices D such that all vertices are either in D or adjacent to a vertex in D. The dominance complex D(G) is the collection of complements to dominating sets [CITATION_1] . Note that this is because dominating sets are closed under superset as opposed to subsets.",
